==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[sclave]]'' < [[Medieval Latin]] ''[[sclavus]]'' < Byzantine Greek ''[[sklavos]]'' < Old Slavonic ''[[sloveninu]]'', ''[[slovene]]''. Beyond this, the ultimate etymology has long been a matter of dispute among linguists.

===Noun===
'''Slav'''
# A person of [[Slavic]] origins.

